stateDiagram-v2
  direction LR
  [*] --> DisabledSafe: init

  DisabledSafe --> Ramping: Enable
  Ramping --> EnabledHolding: at target
  EnabledHolding --> Ramping: new target

  EnabledHolding --> DisabledHvOn: DisableImmediate
  Ramping --> DisabledHvOn: DisableImmediate
  EnabledHolding --> DisabledSafe: DisableForce
  Ramping --> DisabledSafe: DisableForce
  DisabledHvOn --> DisabledSafe: DisableForce

  EnabledHolding --> Ramping: fault + DisableGraceful action
  Ramping --> FaultLatched: fault + Immediate/Force action
  EnabledHolding --> FaultLatched: fault + Immediate/Force action
  Ramping --> DisabledSafe: graceful ramp-to-zero done

  FaultLatched --> DisabledSafe: manual Clear Active, any mode
  FaultLatched --> RetryCooldown: Automatic + AUTO_RETRY/AUTO_DERATE_RETRY

  state RetryCooldown {
    [*] --> Waiting
    Waiting --> Waiting: cooldown or unsafe
  }

  RetryCooldown --> Ramping: safe now, retries remain
  RetryCooldown --> FaultLatched: retries exhausted

  note right of RetryCooldown
    Only reachable in Automatic mode.
    Normal mode: FaultLatched only
    exits via manual Clear Active.
  end note
